1 SECTION 2. From the funds appropriated to the State Department
2 of Health in Enrolled House Bill No. 2766 of the 1st Session of the
3 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Two Hundred Thousand Dollars
4 ($200,000.00) shall be used for the operations of the Oklahoma State
5 Athletic Commission, pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma
6 State Athletic Commission Act.
7 SECTION 3. From the funds appropriated to the State Department
8 of Health in Enrolled House Bill No. 2766 of the 1st Session of the
9 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Three Million Dollars
10 ($3,000,000.00) shall be disbursed to health centers authorized
11 under Section 330 of the Public Health Service Act, and incorporated
12 in the State of Oklahoma. Any disbursement shall be for the purpose
13 of increasing access to primary health care which may include
14 medical, dental, and/or mental health and substance abuse treatment
15 services in or near designated Medically Underserved Areas or
16 Medically Underserved Populations. Any disbursement for increased
17 access to primary health care services shall be supported by data
18 according to proportions of patient volume and access for the
19 uninsured. The method of disbursement shall be developed by the
20 State Department of Health. The State Commissioner of Health is
21 authorized to promulgate the method of disbursement into rules.
22 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
